citeinfo.title: Metro Stations 2000, Arlington County, VA

descript.abstract: This polygoin represents Census 2000 Metro Station boundaries in Arlington County, VA.
descript.purpose: 2000 Census boundaries represent a hierarchy of statistical areas used to report and summarize demographic information. Census blocks are the smallest, most basic unit of the census geography. Blocks are aggregated into block groups, and those in turn into census tracts. Additionally, these feature classes contain areas the County has identified that define Metro corridors and station areas (a subset of the corridors). The attributes facilitate linking the block, block group and tract regions to external data tables storing demographic data useful for thematic mapping and analysis. Annotation is also available for most of these feature classes.
